WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.410 --> 00:00:04.507
[Ranger] <i>Nations. kingdoms. tribes.
they're all the same</i>.

2
00:00:04.592 --> 00:00:07.610
<i>Can't be a part of any of them
without giving up a piece of your soul.</i>

3
00:00:07.695 --> 00:00:09.926
You are making a mistake.
I am not a witch!

4
00:00:10.010 --> 00:00:11.625
- [screaming]
- We send your corrupt soul

5
00:00:11.710 --> 00:00:13.545
back to the devil himself!

6
00:00:13.722 --> 00:00:14.806
They can't do this.

7
00:00:14.890 --> 00:00:17.507
Lieutenant Commander Tormada of Base 3.

8
00:00:17.601 --> 00:00:21.354
Why would the military send
a scientist out to the front lines?

9
00:00:21.438 --> 00:00:24.274
Because science is
gonna save you. Colonel.

10
00:00:24.358 --> 00:00:26.901
- [screaming. grunting]
<i>- Science is gonna win this war.</i>

11
00:00:26.985 --> 00:00:28.236
[screams]

12
00:00:28.320 --> 00:00:29.571
- [baby crying]
- It's a boy.

13
00:00:29.655 --> 00:00:31.030
- [Sibeth] <i>We'll name him Wolffe.</i>
- [sighs]

14
00:00:31.114 --> 00:00:32.907
[Maghra]
<i>We will not be handing her over today.</i>

15
00:00:32.991 --> 00:00:36.369
A queen who gives away her own sister
in the name of peace will appear weak.

16
00:00:36.453 --> 00:00:37.704
Not this sister.

17
00:00:37.788 --> 00:00:40.331
[Maghra] <i>I know the ambassador
is more than a little fond of you.</i>

18
00:00:40.415 --> 00:00:42.584
She's not completely immune to my charms.

19
00:00:42.668 --> 00:00:44.919
[Maghra] <i>Well. then. you'll have to be
exceedingly charming.</i>

20
00:00:45.003 --> 00:00:46.732
Lion! [Grunts]

21
00:00:47.503 --> 00:00:51.735
[Wren] <i>So this all ends with us
killing Baba Voss and conquering Paya?</i>

22
00:00:52.974 --> 00:00:58.123
<i>Singing "Lullaby"...</i>

23
00:01:00.520 --> 00:01:03.750
- [high-pitched ringing]
- [creaking]

24
00:01:07.737 --> 00:01:11.176
[dog barking]

25
00:01:11.866 --> 00:01:14.554
[groaning]

26
00:01:15.953 --> 00:01:17.037
[grunts]

27
00:01:17.121 --> 00:01:18.808
- Ranger!
- [Ranger] Baba!

28
00:01:19.749 --> 00:01:22.960
[Baba Voss groans] Lion. Where's Lion?

29
00:01:23.044 --> 00:01:25.045
- [grunts]
- [Baba Voss] Help me up.

30
00:01:25.129 --> 00:01:27.400
- Watch my arm. [Groans. strains]
- [dog barks]

31
00:01:27.798 --> 00:01:30.008
- [groaning. breathing heavily]
- Here. Here.

32
00:01:30.092 --> 00:01:31.321
[Lu groans]

33
00:01:32.511 --> 00:01:34.574
Lion! [Pants]

34
00:01:35.473 --> 00:01:36.618
Lion!

35
00:01:37.224 --> 00:01:40.227
- [Ranger] Baba. Lulu?
- [fingers snapping]

36
00:01:40.311 --> 00:01:42.803
[Baba Voss panting] Here.

37
00:01:42.888 --> 00:01:44.116
I'm sorry.

38
00:01:49.195 --> 00:01:52.281
[Ranger]
Whatever that was. it tore her to pieces.

39
00:01:52.365 --> 00:01:54.950
[groaning]

40
00:01:55.034 --> 00:01:57.661
[inhales sharply. exhales]

41
00:01:57.745 --> 00:01:59.371
[breathes heavily]

42
00:01:59.455 --> 00:02:01.267
What kind of creature did this?

43
00:02:02.124 --> 00:02:03.520
They were Trivantians.

44
00:02:03.917 --> 00:02:05.605
[Ranger] This far from the border?

45
00:02:06.837 --> 00:02:09.172
It was revenge. For Edo.

46
00:02:09.256 --> 00:02:11.383
- So they were here for you.
- [Ranger] Lu.

47
00:02:11.467 --> 00:02:14.177
I told you
he would bring death to our door.

48
00:02:14.261 --> 00:02:16.596
[sucks teeth. grunts]

49
00:02:16.680 --> 00:02:20.119
[grunting. panting]

50
00:02:23.604 --> 00:02:24.916
I'm sorry about that.

51
00:02:28.609 --> 00:02:32.549
She's not wrong. [Breathes heavily]

52
00:02:34.031 --> 00:02:35.468
I brought them here.

53
00:02:36.492 --> 00:02:37.971
And now Bow Lion is dead.

54
00:02:39.745 --> 00:02:41.121
[sighs]

55
00:02:41.205 --> 00:02:42.767
It doesn't make sense.

56
00:02:43.791 --> 00:02:46.418
If I'm the Trivantians.
and I have this kind of power.

57
00:02:46.502 --> 00:02:48.356
why wait until now to use it?

58
00:02:49.505 --> 00:02:50.672
Could've obliterated you

59
00:02:50.756 --> 00:02:52.986
and all the armies of Paya
at Green hill Gap.

60
00:02:56.512 --> 00:02:57.907
They didn't have it yet.

61
00:02:59.807 --> 00:03:00.952
And now they do.

62
00:03:03.686 --> 00:03:04.831
And now they do.

63
00:03:05.563 --> 00:03:07.897
[Tamacti Jun] Nellicut. Wallen and Yarnes.

64
00:03:07.981 --> 00:03:10.359
- [Maghra] You know them?
- Yes.

65
00:03:10.443 --> 00:03:13.153
All Witchfinders once under my command.

66
00:03:13.237 --> 00:03:17.218
These are the men who killed Row Vano.
Followers of Lucien Bray.

67
00:03:20.828 --> 00:03:24.392
[bells jingling]

68
00:03:26.250 --> 00:03:28.771
Punishment for murder is death.

69
00:03:29.170 --> 00:03:32.297
The punishment for being a witch is death.

70
00:03:32.381 --> 00:03:34.299
If there were witches.
which there are not.

71
00:03:34.383 --> 00:03:35.968
that law no longer exists.

72
00:03:36.052 --> 00:03:37.344
[Wallen] You may be queen.

73
00:03:37.428 --> 00:03:39.449
but you are not our god.

74
00:03:40.681 --> 00:03:44.142
You simply saying something doesn't exist
does not make it so.

75
00:03:44.226 --> 00:03:47.540
[Maghra] It was spoken words
that declared them witches to begin with.

76
00:03:48.230 --> 00:03:50.043
Words from the one true God.

77
00:03:50.816 --> 00:03:52.921
and not the mother of witches.

78
00:03:53.361 --> 00:03:55.153
- Heretic! [Spits]
- [Tamacti Jun gasps]

79
00:03:55.237 --> 00:03:57.614
[shouts. panting] You fool.

80
00:03:57.698 --> 00:03:59.992
Lucien Bray cares nothing for you.

81
00:04:00.076 --> 00:04:03.161
He'll welcome your deaths
as martyrs for his cause.

82
00:04:03.245 --> 00:04:05.808
I was trying to save your lives.

83
00:04:06.248 --> 00:04:09.751
This is where a smarter man would've
begged mercy from a merciful queen.

84
00:04:09.835 --> 00:04:12.170
Instead. you're gonna hang.

85
00:04:12.254 --> 00:04:13.672
Not for your beliefs.

86
00:04:13.756 --> 00:04:15.674
but because you're idiots.

87
00:04:15.758 --> 00:04:17.111
[grunts]

88
00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:25.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

89
00:04:26.018 --> 00:04:27.019
Tamacti.

90
00:04:27.103 --> 00:04:28.604
How can I sentence them to death

91
00:04:28.688 --> 00:04:31.231
when I spare my own sister.
who murdered hundreds?

92
00:04:31.315 --> 00:04:34.568
- [Tamacti Jun] They did burn a man alive.
- She's done so much worse.

93
00:04:34.652 --> 00:04:36.028
[Tamacti Jun] Maybe when they're killed.

94
00:04:36.112 --> 00:04:38.383
you can find it within yourself
to deal with Sibeth.

95
00:04:41.367 --> 00:04:44.328
So you think
I should kill them for practice?

96
00:04:44.412 --> 00:04:50.083
No. What I'm saying is their deaths serve
a greater good. law and order.

97
00:04:50.167 --> 00:04:54.482
And if your sister's death is
the pathway to peace with Trivantes…

98
00:04:54.964 --> 00:04:57.777
So this has nothing to do with
her crimes against you.

99
00:04:58.634 --> 00:05:00.697
I understand why you might think that.

100
00:05:01.137 --> 00:05:04.097
But remember.
I didn't ask for this position.

101
00:05:04.181 --> 00:05:05.223
I didn't even want it.

102
00:05:05.307 --> 00:05:07.036
I didn't want this one either.

103
00:05:07.601 --> 00:05:11.291
Well. then.
we can be miserable fools together.

104
00:05:17.861 --> 00:05:19.716
[breathes heavily]

105
00:05:32.126 --> 00:05:33.813
[sighs]

106
00:05:43.471 --> 00:05:45.366
[sighs]

107
00:05:53.022 --> 00:05:55.543
You're thinking of going back
down the mountain.

108
00:05:57.234 --> 00:06:00.757
[sighs] They did not bring the God Thunder
this far east just to kill me.

109
00:06:01.781 --> 00:06:03.968
The Trivantians will be moving on Paya.

110
00:06:04.408 --> 00:06:05.637
Maybe.

111
00:06:06.452 --> 00:06:08.306
That's a problem for down there.

112
00:06:09.205 --> 00:06:12.435
It will be a problem up here
when the Trivantian army arrives.

113
00:06:12.958 --> 00:06:14.812
It seems as if they already have.

114
00:06:18.547 --> 00:06:19.798
I am sorry about your home.

115
00:06:19.882 --> 00:06:21.967
[Ranger inhales deeply]

116
00:06:22.051 --> 00:06:23.321
I can build another.

117
00:06:25.679 --> 00:06:28.952
[inhales sharply]
I have to go warn Maghra.

118
00:06:32.103 --> 00:06:35.625
[Ranger breathes deeply]

119
00:06:36.232 --> 00:06:37.710
Then this is goodbye.

120
00:06:39.860 --> 00:06:41.422
[fingers snapping]

121
00:06:41.987 --> 00:06:43.383
Thank you for everything.

122
00:06:44.073 --> 00:06:46.450
[sniffs. sighs]

123
00:06:46.534 --> 00:06:49.138
Your wound smells clean.
It should heal nicely.

124
00:06:50.079 --> 00:06:51.391
[groans]

125
00:06:52.623 --> 00:06:55.645
- Remember… stay alive.
- [grunts]

126
00:06:58.421 --> 00:07:00.275
Beware of wolves. Baba Voss.

127
00:07:01.132 --> 00:07:03.152
[Baba Voss] Beware of wolves. Ranger.

128
00:07:14.812 --> 00:07:15.957
Goodbye. Lion.

129
00:08:47.113 --> 00:08:49.467
[blade sharpening]

130
00:09:06.090 --> 00:09:07.235
Who approaches?

131
00:09:09.093 --> 00:09:13.639
[Tamacti Jun] Those who used to serve
under me still know my voice.

132
00:09:13.723 --> 00:09:16.870
We no longer recognize
your authority. heretic.

133
00:09:17.351 --> 00:09:23.585
Regardless. Shiloh. I'm confident
your skull will recognize my blade.

134
00:09:24.233 --> 00:09:25.920
What do you want. Tamacti Jun?

135
00:09:26.610 --> 00:09:29.215
Just a word… with you.

136
00:09:29.697 --> 00:09:31.657
[Lucien] We all swore the same oath.

137
00:09:31.741 --> 00:09:36.472
I can't imagine you take any pleasure
in fighting your brothers and sisters.

138
00:09:37.078 --> 00:09:38.497
I do not.

139
00:09:38.581 --> 00:09:40.749
Yet you arrested three of us

140
00:09:40.833 --> 00:09:43.813
who now await execution
by your heretic queen.

141
00:09:44.295 --> 00:09:48.026
It was you who sent these men
to their deaths.

142
00:09:49.133 --> 00:09:51.237
[Lucien] They upheld their sacred vow.

143
00:09:51.761 --> 00:09:54.908
I'm sure that'll be of great comfort
to their families.

144
00:09:55.473 --> 00:09:59.454
How many more of your own people
will you sacrifice?

145
00:10:00.102 --> 00:10:01.539
As many as it takes.

146
00:10:04.023 --> 00:10:06.544
And you should be standing
right here beside me.

147
00:10:06.901 --> 00:10:08.527
Your queen has sinned before God...

148
00:10:08.611 --> 00:10:10.632
Not here to debate!

149
00:10:13.366 --> 00:10:14.511
Pathetic.

150
00:10:16.869 --> 00:10:18.181
This ends today.

151
00:10:20.164 --> 00:10:24.229
No more speeches. No more gatherings.

152
00:10:25.086 --> 00:10:28.358
Retire in silence.

153
00:10:30.466 --> 00:10:31.778
And if I don't?

154
00:10:39.266 --> 00:10:41.246
Then I will retire you.

155
00:10:45.856 --> 00:10:47.669
I was hoping you might say that.

156
00:11:02.248 --> 00:11:04.477
[both grunting. shouting]

157
00:11:09.505 --> 00:11:10.775
[Lucien shouts]

158
00:11:13.050 --> 00:11:14.259
[shouts]

159
00:11:14.343 --> 00:11:16.303
- [Tamacti Jun grunts]
- [shouts]

160
00:11:16.387 --> 00:11:18.491
[panting]

161
00:11:19.432 --> 00:11:20.932
- [Tamacti Jun shouts]
- [grunts]

162
00:11:21.016 --> 00:11:23.288
[both straining]

163
00:11:26.355 --> 00:11:27.499
[shouts]

164
00:11:30.192 --> 00:11:31.462
[both grunting]

165
00:11:31.986 --> 00:11:33.131
[bone cracks]

166
00:11:33.904 --> 00:11:35.425
[pants. grunts]

167
00:11:38.492 --> 00:11:40.138
[both grunting]

168
00:11:42.121 --> 00:11:43.266
[groans]

169
00:11:45.583 --> 00:11:48.479
[both grunting. panting. straining]

170
00:11:51.172 --> 00:11:53.966
[panting]

171
00:11:54.050 --> 00:11:55.904
You've gotten slow in your old age.

172
00:12:02.725 --> 00:12:04.829
- [groans]
- Still too fast for you.

173
00:12:06.854 --> 00:12:08.791
[both grunting]

174
00:12:09.440 --> 00:12:11.692
- [Tamacti Jun shouts]
- [groans]

175
00:12:11.776 --> 00:12:13.880
[both panting]

176
00:12:14.612 --> 00:12:16.549
- Lucien!
- Stand down!

177
00:12:17.573 --> 00:12:20.053
[Lucien panting]

178
00:12:20.868 --> 00:12:22.619
You were a soldier of God.

179
00:12:22.703 --> 00:12:23.973
A man of faith.

180
00:12:24.455 --> 00:12:25.892
What happened to you?

181
00:12:26.332 --> 00:12:27.874
I died. Lucien.

182
00:12:27.958 --> 00:12:29.167
[panting]

183
00:12:29.251 --> 00:12:32.023
I went to the place where the dead go.

184
00:12:33.297 --> 00:12:37.403
And I've got to tell you.
it wasn't as we were told.

185
00:12:39.720 --> 00:12:42.659
I was disappointed.

186
00:12:44.225 --> 00:12:45.370
You were bewitched!

187
00:12:45.810 --> 00:12:49.438
[sighs] Brother.
you don't know the half of it.

188
00:12:49.522 --> 00:12:51.857
[breathes heavily] What...

189
00:12:51.941 --> 00:12:54.587
- [grunts]
- [shouting]

190
00:12:56.487 --> 00:12:58.633
[Tamacti Jun breathing heavily]

191
00:13:01.575 --> 00:13:02.929
Go home.

192
00:13:05.496 --> 00:13:06.830
All of you.

193
00:13:06.914 --> 00:13:09.249
[Lucien breathing heavily]

194
00:13:09.333 --> 00:13:12.480
[Tamacti Jun] This church is closed.

195
00:13:17.425 --> 00:13:20.613
- [Harlan breathing heavily]
- [Trovere moaning]

196
00:13:23.222 --> 00:13:27.351
- [screaming. moaning]
- [Harlan grunting]

197
00:13:27.435 --> 00:13:30.165
- [sighs]
- [both panting]

198
00:13:31.564 --> 00:13:33.357
You're very good at that.

199
00:13:33.441 --> 00:13:37.297
- I like to think I'm a considerate host.
- Ah. but I'm still angry with you.

200
00:13:37.987 --> 00:13:39.488
You don't seem angry.

201
00:13:39.572 --> 00:13:41.551
I shouldn't be here anymore.

202
00:13:42.366 --> 00:13:43.659
Well. I'm pleased that you are.

203
00:13:43.743 --> 00:13:45.285
I'm serious.

204
00:13:45.369 --> 00:13:48.914
I should be back in Trivantes
with Sibeth in chains. [Sighs]

205
00:13:48.998 --> 00:13:50.874
I'll have her for you soon enough.

206
00:13:50.958 --> 00:13:53.021
[both breathing heavily]

207
00:13:54.378 --> 00:13:58.234
My government is not known
for being patient. Harlan.

208
00:14:00.051 --> 00:14:03.220
Well. in my experience.

209
00:14:03.304 --> 00:14:07.368
patience. like most things.
comes at a price.

210
00:14:09.685 --> 00:14:11.478
Keep talking. [Breathes heavily]

211
00:14:11.562 --> 00:14:16.961
I will arrange for an extra shipment
of coal to be transported immediately

212
00:14:17.651 --> 00:14:19.589
at half the regular price.

213
00:14:21.238 --> 00:14:22.383
At no cost.

214
00:14:24.617 --> 00:14:26.221
As I said. no cost.

215
00:14:26.660 --> 00:14:28.078
[breathes heavily. swallows]

216
00:14:28.162 --> 00:14:32.060
And another such shipment
for every day your queen stalls.

217
00:14:32.792 --> 00:14:35.002
- [grunts]
- Are you trying to break me?

218
00:14:35.086 --> 00:14:37.337
Oh. on the contrary.

219
00:14:37.421 --> 00:14:39.943
Maghra has clearly asked you
to convince me.

220
00:14:40.549 --> 00:14:43.196
Now I'm offering you
an incentive to convince her.

221
00:14:46.263 --> 00:14:48.724
I suppose it's the least I can do
in the name of peace.

222
00:14:48.808 --> 00:14:50.267
Mmm. that's the spirit.

223
00:14:50.351 --> 00:14:53.206
[inhales deeply]
Now you can get back to convincing me.

224
00:14:56.315 --> 00:14:57.585
[Wolffe cooing]

225
00:14:59.026 --> 00:15:02.090
[Maghra] He eats more
than both the twins did combined.

226
00:15:04.073 --> 00:15:05.198
If you left him here.

227
00:15:05.282 --> 00:15:07.554
you wouldn't be burdened
with his crying for me.

228
00:15:09.995 --> 00:15:12.100
It's not as if I'm going anywhere.

229
00:15:12.623 --> 00:15:14.227
Soothing Wolffe is not a burden.

230
00:15:14.792 --> 00:15:16.354
Visiting you is the chore.

231
00:15:19.755 --> 00:15:23.050
So I hear you've arrested the Witchfinders
who defied my edict.

232
00:15:23.134 --> 00:15:24.362
Good for you.

233
00:15:26.262 --> 00:15:27.262
[scoffs]

234
00:15:27.346 --> 00:15:29.909
Tell me. when will they be executed?

235
00:15:31.058 --> 00:15:32.745
Don't waver now. Maghra.

236
00:15:34.270 --> 00:15:36.438
You'll confirm the weakness
of your character to all.

237
00:15:36.522 --> 00:15:37.898
The council will eat you alive.

238
00:15:37.982 --> 00:15:41.421
Some might think of the sparing of lives
as strength of character.

239
00:15:42.028 --> 00:15:45.008
No. they won't. Not from you.

240
00:15:45.656 --> 00:15:50.410
As queen. sometimes you have to do things
others might consider evil.

241
00:15:50.494 --> 00:15:52.537
even you might consider evil.

242
00:15:52.621 --> 00:15:54.517
for the good of the kingdom.

243
00:15:57.710 --> 00:16:00.857
You serve no one
if you don't enforce the law.

244
00:16:03.591 --> 00:16:06.843
No one would've dared do what these
Witchfinders did while I was queen.

245
00:16:06.927 --> 00:16:09.199
[inhales deeply. stammers]

246
00:16:11.682 --> 00:16:15.205
And if I felt it necessary for any reason

247
00:16:15.811 --> 00:16:19.564
to pledge the sacrifice
of my own sister to the enemy…

248
00:16:19.648 --> 00:16:21.275
[whispering] No.

249
00:16:21.359 --> 00:16:23.485
…I'd make damn sure
I fulfilled that promise.

250
00:16:23.569 --> 00:16:26.007
You don't know what you're talking about.

251
00:16:26.405 --> 00:16:31.827
I know the Trivantians arrived a day ago.
and yet here I am. alive and well.

252
00:16:31.911 --> 00:16:35.600
- You're here 'cause the baby needs to eat.
- [scoffs. chuckles]

253
00:16:36.499 --> 00:16:39.395
You have plenty of wet nurses.

254
00:16:39.835 --> 00:16:45.610
Would you really use my son
as an excuse for your own failings?

255
00:16:47.426 --> 00:16:51.346
If I were in your place.
I'd have handed them your head already.

256
00:16:51.430 --> 00:16:53.117
They don't want your head. Sibeth.

257
00:16:53.641 --> 00:16:56.371
They want you. Alive.

258
00:16:57.937 --> 00:16:58.979
And don't worry.

259
00:16:59.063 --> 00:17:00.606
I'll be out of excuses soon enough.

260
00:17:00.690 --> 00:17:02.794
and then you'll be
on your way to Trivantes.

261
00:17:03.693 --> 00:17:05.964
I'll be back when the baby's done nursing.

262
00:17:09.073 --> 00:17:10.718
[fingers snapping]

263
00:17:24.046 --> 00:17:26.192
[soldier snoring]

264
00:17:35.433 --> 00:17:36.619
[soldier snorts]

265
00:17:37.685 --> 00:17:39.372
[snoring continues]

266
00:18:16.098 --> 00:18:17.618
Don't raise your voice.

267
00:18:19.225 --> 00:18:20.371
[sighs]

268
00:18:21.520 --> 00:18:22.665
[grunts]

269
00:18:25.107 --> 00:18:26.252
You.

270
00:18:29.653 --> 00:18:30.798
You can see?

271
00:18:33.324 --> 00:18:34.802
You're Jerlamarel's son.

272
00:18:36.035 --> 00:18:37.180
Oloman. right?

273
00:18:38.579 --> 00:18:39.724
I know your sister…

274
00:18:40.790 --> 00:18:41.790
Haniwa.

275
00:18:41.874 --> 00:18:43.019
Haniwa?

276
00:18:44.210 --> 00:18:45.355
[scoffs]

277
00:18:47.380 --> 00:18:48.650
Is she alive?

278
00:18:50.424 --> 00:18:52.278
She doesn't like you very much.

279
00:18:55.805 --> 00:18:57.283
No. I'm sure she doesn't.

280
00:18:58.224 --> 00:19:02.144
- Those fire weapons. You made them?
- [sighs]

281
00:19:02.228 --> 00:19:03.665
I had no choice.

282
00:19:06.107 --> 00:19:07.502
Well. you have one now.

283
00:19:07.900 --> 00:19:09.985
- What are you doing?
- I'm cutting you free.

284
00:19:10.069 --> 00:19:11.339
No. no. no. Stop.

285
00:19:12.446 --> 00:19:15.301
[sighs] You don't understand.
They have my family.

286
00:19:17.368 --> 00:19:19.013
If I run. they'll kill them.

287
00:19:20.496 --> 00:19:22.267
Same way they killed my father.

288
00:19:23.499 --> 00:19:25.228
Tormada killed Jerlamarel?

289
00:19:26.794 --> 00:19:27.939
No.

290
00:19:30.381 --> 00:19:31.651
Edo Voss did.

291
00:19:33.217 --> 00:19:34.362
Edo?

292
00:19:37.054 --> 00:19:38.241
Are you sure?

293
00:19:39.390 --> 00:19:41.286
[sighs] I was there.

294
00:19:44.979 --> 00:19:46.124
[exhales sharply]

295
00:19:47.523 --> 00:19:50.837
- Those weapons?
- Technology of the ancients.

296
00:19:51.610 --> 00:19:53.923
Compressed coal
that explodes when ignited.

297
00:19:54.864 --> 00:19:55.864
They're called bombs.

298
00:19:55.948 --> 00:19:57.927
I don't care what they're called.

299
00:19:58.576 --> 00:20:00.369
You have to stop making them.

300
00:20:00.453 --> 00:20:01.598
Thousands will die.

301
00:20:03.914 --> 00:20:05.643
Where's your family being held?

302
00:20:06.333 --> 00:20:08.021
At my father's compound.

303
00:20:10.296 --> 00:20:12.233
[inhales deeply] Okay.

304
00:20:14.133 --> 00:20:15.737
I will get you out of here.

305
00:20:16.469 --> 00:20:18.364
You'll go free your family.

306
00:20:18.971 --> 00:20:20.658
And I'll go back to Trivantes.

307
00:20:21.182 --> 00:20:24.309
When the Triangle learns Tormada's been
working with the sighted to build weapons.

308
00:20:24.393 --> 00:20:26.581
he'll be stripped of his rank
and put on trial.

309
00:20:26.937 --> 00:20:29.083
[sighs]

310
00:20:29.523 --> 00:20:30.668
You're wrong.

311
00:20:32.026 --> 00:20:33.171
What?

312
00:20:33.652 --> 00:20:36.174
Tormada just ended the Ganite War.

313
00:20:37.031 --> 00:20:38.782
He'll be given a hero's welcome.

314
00:20:38.866 --> 00:20:40.887
- He broke the law.
- He won.

315
00:20:42.078 --> 00:20:43.078
[sighs]

316
00:20:43.162 --> 00:20:44.913
Besides. we've already built
many more bombs.

317
00:20:44.997 --> 00:20:46.142
[soldier coughs]

318
00:20:49.502 --> 00:20:50.647
[sighs]

319
00:20:54.340 --> 00:20:55.485
How many?

320
00:20:57.468 --> 00:20:58.613
Hundreds.

321
00:21:00.304 --> 00:21:01.491
[sighs]

322
00:21:03.599 --> 00:21:06.663
Okay. new plan.

323
00:21:07.895 --> 00:21:09.582
We go free your family.

324
00:21:11.273 --> 00:21:13.127
Then we destroy the bombs.

325
00:21:27.289 --> 00:21:28.434
[inhales sharply]

326
00:21:30.167 --> 00:21:32.230
[Maddox] Tormada will be disappointed.

327
00:21:32.628 --> 00:21:34.004
He had such high hopes for you.

328
00:21:34.088 --> 00:21:35.756
- [Wren grunts. screams]
- [shouts]

329
00:21:35.840 --> 00:21:38.319
- [Wren straining]
- [shouts]

330
00:21:38.718 --> 00:21:40.761
[Wren straining. choking]

331
00:21:40.845 --> 00:21:43.347
He'll have your corpse to study at least.

332
00:21:43.431 --> 00:21:46.160
[laughing]

333
00:21:46.600 --> 00:21:49.770
[groans. laughing]

334
00:21:49.854 --> 00:21:52.230
[groans. grunts]

335
00:21:52.314 --> 00:21:53.543
Oloman!

336
00:21:55.317 --> 00:21:56.880
[screams]

337
00:21:57.236 --> 00:21:58.381
[Maddox shouts]

338
00:22:05.786 --> 00:22:08.099
[grunts. panting]

339
00:22:21.510 --> 00:22:23.448
I needed him alive. fools!

340
00:22:23.888 --> 00:22:24.930
Stop her!

341
00:22:25.014 --> 00:22:27.535
Stop! [Shouts indistinctly]

342
00:23:09.058 --> 00:23:10.767
[strains. grunts]

343
00:23:10.851 --> 00:23:12.622
You're getting pretty good at that.

344
00:23:13.145 --> 00:23:14.874
- [horse whinnies]
- Thanks.

345
00:23:17.108 --> 00:23:18.419
Is that Toad's horse?

346
00:23:19.360 --> 00:23:20.505
Yes.

347
00:23:22.947 --> 00:23:25.593
Did you ever imagine
you'd miss a Witchfinder?

348
00:23:27.034 --> 00:23:29.264
I could never have imagined any of this.

349
00:23:31.455 --> 00:23:32.600
Do you mean Wolffe?

350
00:23:34.083 --> 00:23:35.895
- Don't.
- Kofun.

351
00:23:37.545 --> 00:23:39.983
[breathing heavily]

352
00:23:43.175 --> 00:23:44.320
[grunts]

353
00:23:45.302 --> 00:23:46.887
[Charlotte] He's going through a lot.

354
00:23:46.971 --> 00:23:49.264
[Haniwa sighs]

355
00:23:49.348 --> 00:23:50.994
He is too sensitive.

356
00:23:52.518 --> 00:23:54.581
Or maybe you're not sensitive enough.

357
00:23:56.355 --> 00:24:00.461
Must you speak every thought
that pops into your head? [Sighs]

358
00:24:01.360 --> 00:24:04.090
Kofun became a father before he was ready.

359
00:24:04.989 --> 00:24:06.926
<i>He feels ashamed and confused.</i>

360
00:24:08.451 --> 00:24:10.513
So why is he punishing me?

361
00:24:10.870 --> 00:24:12.162
It's not my fault.

362
00:24:12.246 --> 00:24:15.018
No. but it is your responsibility.

363
00:24:16.751 --> 00:24:19.461
<i>Feeling responsible for someone
can be a great weight.</i>

364
00:24:19.545 --> 00:24:20.587
[sighs]

365
00:24:20.671 --> 00:24:22.025
<i>Kofun has his son.</i>

366
00:24:23.132 --> 00:24:24.444
<i>You have Kofun.</i>

367
00:24:25.843 --> 00:24:27.344
<i>And I've got you.</i>

368
00:24:27.428 --> 00:24:28.887
- [Kofun sighs]
- [Charlotte scoffs]

369
00:24:28.971 --> 00:24:30.950
And how often do you punish me for that?

370
00:24:34.977 --> 00:24:37.457
I'm sorry. I don't mean to.

371
00:24:41.901 --> 00:24:43.421
[sighs deeply]

372
00:24:44.862 --> 00:24:46.633
Everything is a mess.

373
00:24:47.031 --> 00:24:48.384
[Charlotte sighs]

374
00:24:49.158 --> 00:24:50.845
You're thinking of Row Vano.

375
00:24:52.953 --> 00:24:54.557
They burned him alive.

376
00:24:56.749 --> 00:24:58.353
They would have burned me too.

377
00:24:58.709 --> 00:24:59.854
[Charlotte] Hey.

378
00:25:01.545 --> 00:25:04.317
I will never let that happen.

379
00:25:08.177 --> 00:25:10.345
Don't they understand
how much easier it would be

380
00:25:10.429 --> 00:25:11.824
for me to kill them?

381
00:25:12.890 --> 00:25:14.224
[chuckles]

382
00:25:14.308 --> 00:25:16.621
[Haniwa]
<i>I could kill ten a day if I wanted.</i>

383
00:25:16.977 --> 00:25:18.623
<i>From a hundred feet away.</i>

384
00:25:19.939 --> 00:25:21.876
<i>They would never know who it was.</i>

385
00:25:23.818 --> 00:25:26.339
And then you would be
everything they fear you are.

386
00:25:28.531 --> 00:25:31.719
I think maybe they should start fearing us
more than they do.

387
00:25:37.331 --> 00:25:38.476
Kofun.

388
00:25:40.626 --> 00:25:44.023
Are you gonna keep standing there
pretending you don't have a son?

389
00:25:45.881 --> 00:25:47.049
[Sibeth sighs]

390
00:25:47.133 --> 00:25:48.425
Jerlamarel had his failings.

391
00:25:48.509 --> 00:25:50.822
but at least
he never denied your existence.

392
00:26:01.272 --> 00:26:02.584
[Sibeth] Mmm.

393
00:26:04.275 --> 00:26:06.693
[sighs. chuckles]

394
00:26:06.777 --> 00:26:07.922
Come here.

395
00:26:09.822 --> 00:26:11.885
- Feel him in your arms.
- I-I can't.

396
00:26:14.201 --> 00:26:15.346
Try.

397
00:26:16.746 --> 00:26:19.100
- Huh? [Chuckles]
- [Wolffe cooing]

398
00:26:19.874 --> 00:26:24.063
[Kofun breathing shakily]

399
00:26:24.587 --> 00:26:25.982
[Sibeth sighs]

400
00:26:27.465 --> 00:26:28.757
[chuckles]

401
00:26:28.841 --> 00:26:29.986
You made him.

402
00:26:35.598 --> 00:26:36.993
[chuckles lightly]

403
00:26:38.225 --> 00:26:40.227
[Sibeth]
I understand this is difficult for you.

404
00:26:40.311 --> 00:26:42.165
but we are your family now.

405
00:26:42.646 --> 00:26:45.293
It falls to you to protect Wolffie.

406
00:26:46.734 --> 00:26:48.254
And his mother.

407
00:26:55.201 --> 00:26:56.387
Kofun. stay.

408
00:26:57.453 --> 00:26:58.662
This is where you belong!

409
00:26:58.746 --> 00:27:00.975
- Kofun. what are you do... [gasps]
- I'm leaving.

410
00:27:03.250 --> 00:27:05.063
[Sibeth] Trouble in paradise.

411
00:27:05.419 --> 00:27:06.981
Haven't you hurt him enough?

412
00:27:07.505 --> 00:27:08.755
[Sibeth] Hurt him?

413
00:27:08.839 --> 00:27:10.132
I mothered his child.

414
00:27:10.216 --> 00:27:12.654
I... I gave him purpose.

415
00:27:13.010 --> 00:27:14.447
[Wolffe cooing]

416
00:27:14.970 --> 00:27:16.115
What is it in you?

417
00:27:17.348 --> 00:27:20.286
This thing that needs to strike
at everyone around you.

418
00:27:22.812 --> 00:27:23.957
I don't know.

419
00:27:25.356 --> 00:27:29.087
Might be the same thing
that gave me the strength to rule.

420
00:27:29.860 --> 00:27:32.090
That strength you so sorely lack.

421
00:27:32.530 --> 00:27:33.675
I loved you.

422
00:27:34.532 --> 00:27:36.386
[clicks tongue] And you still do.

423
00:27:36.909 --> 00:27:38.972
[Wolffe crying]

424
00:27:41.288 --> 00:27:43.560
Oh. Wolffe. It's all right.

425
00:27:45.000 --> 00:27:47.897
It was wrong of me
to allow you this time with Wolffe.

426
00:27:49.255 --> 00:27:50.775
You'll only corrupt him.

427
00:27:51.882 --> 00:27:53.194
As you have my son.

428
00:27:54.260 --> 00:27:57.137
I'm not done feeding him. Maghra.

429
00:27:57.221 --> 00:27:59.056
- [whispering] It's all right.
- Give him back.

430
00:27:59.140 --> 00:28:00.390
[Maghra] It's all right.

431
00:28:00.474 --> 00:28:03.246
- He needs his mother.
- He will never know his mother.

432
00:28:04.645 --> 00:28:06.291
I'm done with you. Sibeth.

433
00:28:07.106 --> 00:28:11.045
You want me to show strength?
I'll start here.

434
00:28:11.610 --> 00:28:12.986
Guard!

435
00:28:13.070 --> 00:28:14.215
[Sibeth] Maghra?

436
00:28:18.576 --> 00:28:19.721
Maghra!

437
00:28:30.629 --> 00:28:34.675
[Harlan] I'm sure the queen will be
joining us in a matter of heartbeats.

438
00:28:34.759 --> 00:28:36.885
[Trovere chuckles]
You'll forgive me if I'm less confident.

439
00:28:36.969 --> 00:28:39.304
given the queen hasn't deigned
to grant me an audience until now.

440
00:28:39.388 --> 00:28:40.722
[Harlan] She means no offense.

441
00:28:40.806 --> 00:28:43.892
It's been a particularly bad day.

442
00:28:43.976 --> 00:28:45.121
A bad day?

443
00:28:45.978 --> 00:28:50.251
If I don't have Sibeth in chains soon.
there will be a lot of bad days to follow.

444
00:28:50.900 --> 00:28:52.067
[sighs]

445
00:28:52.151 --> 00:28:54.047
- You seem tense.
- [scoffs]

446
00:28:54.779 --> 00:28:57.698
I am fucking the queen's husband
in enemy territory

447
00:28:57.782 --> 00:29:00.242
while the fates of two nations
hang in the balance.

448
00:29:00.326 --> 00:29:01.743
[sighs deeply]

449
00:29:01.827 --> 00:29:02.911
Fair point.

450
00:29:02.995 --> 00:29:05.099
[exhales sharply] Harlan.

451
00:29:08.000 --> 00:29:10.230
All will be well. okay?

452
00:29:11.045 --> 00:29:12.546
You just need to relax.

453
00:29:12.630 --> 00:29:14.108
You're not making it easy.

454
00:29:15.341 --> 00:29:18.260
You're the one who's fucking
the queen's husband in enemy territory.

455
00:29:18.344 --> 00:29:22.283
My apologies. Ambassador Trovere.
for not greeting you sooner.

456
00:29:23.015 --> 00:29:25.286
It's been a trying time.

457
00:29:26.685 --> 00:29:29.813
Not to worry.
I am well taken care of by Lord Harlan.

458
00:29:29.897 --> 00:29:32.502
Yes. he's much better company than I am.

459
00:29:33.234 --> 00:29:35.152
Will you be joining us. my queen?

460
00:29:35.236 --> 00:29:36.570
Unfortunately not.

461
00:29:36.654 --> 00:29:39.948
There are some pressing affairs of state
that need my immediate attention.

462
00:29:40.032 --> 00:29:41.199
I just wanted to come by

463
00:29:41.283 --> 00:29:43.555
and wish you Godspeed
on your journey home.

464
00:29:44.120 --> 00:29:45.537
I'm sorry. Your Majesty.

465
00:29:45.621 --> 00:29:47.789
I-I would have thought
Lord Harlan conveyed to you

466
00:29:47.873 --> 00:29:50.770
that I cannot leave
until my mandate has been satisfied.

467
00:29:51.752 --> 00:29:53.606
- My sister.
- That's right.

468
00:29:54.880 --> 00:29:57.924
And I can only imagine
how painful this is for you.

469
00:29:58.008 --> 00:29:59.571
You can have her.

470
00:30:00.010 --> 00:30:02.907
She'll be in your hands
by the rise of the God Flame.

471
00:30:04.056 --> 00:30:07.392
Then on behalf of the government
of Trivantes.

472
00:30:07.476 --> 00:30:09.372
I thank you for your hospitality.

473
00:30:09.937 --> 00:30:11.708
Yes. thank you.

474
00:30:12.481 --> 00:30:14.169
[bells jingle]

475
00:30:18.654 --> 00:30:19.966
Well. that was easy.

476
00:30:38.424 --> 00:30:39.569
[sighs]

477
00:30:48.434 --> 00:30:49.768
- Hello?
- [dog barking]

478
00:30:49.852 --> 00:30:51.061
[Baba Voss] Oh.

479
00:30:51.145 --> 00:30:53.522
It's okay. No. no. No.

480
00:30:53.606 --> 00:30:56.211
Good boy. Stay.

481
00:30:57.276 --> 00:30:58.902
- Baba?
- [Baba Voss sighs deeply]

482
00:30:58.986 --> 00:31:01.591
[dog barking]

483
00:31:03.949 --> 00:31:05.784
- [yelps]
- Maghra.

484
00:31:05.868 --> 00:31:08.097
- Maghra. Maghra. please.
- [grunting]

485
00:31:08.496 --> 00:31:11.164
Where were you? [Sniffles]

486
00:31:11.248 --> 00:31:12.894
Why did you leave us?

487
00:31:16.045 --> 00:31:18.024
[Maghra crying. sniffing]

488
00:31:23.844 --> 00:31:25.990
[sniffs]

489
00:31:26.847 --> 00:31:28.159
What happened to you?

490
00:31:29.350 --> 00:31:32.205
[sniffles] They found me.

491
00:31:32.812 --> 00:31:33.957
Who found you?

492
00:31:34.563 --> 00:31:35.917
The Trivantians.

493
00:31:36.273 --> 00:31:37.794
You were in Trivantes?

494
00:31:38.609 --> 00:31:43.258
No. they're here with a... This new weapon.

495
00:31:43.739 --> 00:31:46.553
Something big. uh. like God Thunder.

496
00:31:47.284 --> 00:31:48.452
Fire and force.

497
00:31:48.536 --> 00:31:51.349
It... [sniffles]
It ripped open the ground beneath me.

498
00:31:56.752 --> 00:31:57.981
Bow Lion is dead.

499
00:32:00.381 --> 00:32:03.194
What? What... Why are you...
What are you talking about?

500
00:32:04.385 --> 00:32:07.763
It tore her to more pieces
than I could gather and bury.

501
00:32:07.847 --> 00:32:09.075
All right. All right.

502
00:32:09.849 --> 00:32:11.411
What... What is this weapon?

503
00:32:13.185 --> 00:32:14.414
I don't know.

504
00:32:15.354 --> 00:32:17.292
But they did not build it to kill me.

505
00:32:17.690 --> 00:32:19.399
They will come here to win their war.

506
00:32:19.483 --> 00:32:23.590
Baba. Baba. We are no longer at war.

507
00:32:24.155 --> 00:32:28.261
I've spent the time since you left
negotiating peace with the Trivantians.

508
00:32:29.910 --> 00:32:31.848
Well. then you have been lied to.

509
00:32:33.164 --> 00:32:34.873
While you were negotiating.

510
00:32:34.957 --> 00:32:37.125
those soldiers were
in the Northern Mountains

511
00:32:37.209 --> 00:32:39.731
with weapons
more powerful than you can imagine.

512
00:32:40.337 --> 00:32:42.130
No soldier can stand up to that thunder.

513
00:32:42.214 --> 00:32:44.736
The... The Trivantian ambassador is here.

514
00:32:45.134 --> 00:32:47.594
She seemed intent on achieving peace.

515
00:32:47.678 --> 00:32:49.657
The ambassador is here?

516
00:32:50.222 --> 00:32:51.974
You need to lock her up
and find what you can.

517
00:32:52.058 --> 00:32:56.331
I-I cannot lock up Ambassador Trovere
without any proof.

518
00:32:56.896 --> 00:32:59.626
[scoffs] It would end our treaty
before it's been signed.

519
00:32:59.982 --> 00:33:03.402
You are not listening.
There is no peace. There never was.

520
00:33:03.486 --> 00:33:04.903
- You have been deceived.
- [sighs]

521
00:33:04.987 --> 00:33:08.657
Has it maybe occurred to you
that it is you who's been deceived?

522
00:33:08.741 --> 00:33:11.201
Can you even be sure
it was Trivantians who attacked you?

523
00:33:11.285 --> 00:33:14.079
- Maghra...
- Baba. you've been away for a long time.

524
00:33:14.163 --> 00:33:16.559
You have no idea
what's been happening here.

525
00:33:17.958 --> 00:33:19.103
You're right.

526
00:33:21.170 --> 00:33:22.565
I was not here.

527
00:33:24.840 --> 00:33:27.111
And I will apologize for that later.

528
00:33:27.468 --> 00:33:28.593
[sniffles]

529
00:33:28.677 --> 00:33:33.098
But right now. I am telling you
that there are Trivantian soldiers in Paya

530
00:33:33.182 --> 00:33:37.019
with a weapon
that will tear your kingdom apart.

531
00:33:37.103 --> 00:33:39.438
You need to ready your armies to march.

532
00:33:39.522 --> 00:33:41.231
You would have us go to war?

533
00:33:41.315 --> 00:33:44.693
You're already at war! [Panting]

534
00:33:44.777 --> 00:33:47.237
And the longer you hide from it.
the more we will pay.

535
00:33:47.321 --> 00:33:49.884
[breathing heavily]

536
00:33:53.119 --> 00:33:54.764
[sniffles. growls]

537
00:33:56.038 --> 00:33:57.497
Baba.

538
00:33:57.581 --> 00:33:59.561
- [Baba Voss] No.
- Baba!

539
00:34:17.226 --> 00:34:19.372
[soldier grunting. choking]

540
00:34:20.813 --> 00:34:22.898
[Baba Voss grunting]

541
00:34:22.982 --> 00:34:24.316
Where's the ambassador?

542
00:34:24.400 --> 00:34:26.485
[soldier straining]

543
00:34:26.569 --> 00:34:28.715
Huh? Where is the ambassador?

544
00:34:34.785 --> 00:34:36.723
[straining stops]

545
00:34:42.543 --> 00:34:46.024
[growling]

546
00:35:05.608 --> 00:35:09.546
[soldiers grunting. choking]

547
00:35:36.263 --> 00:35:39.077
- [Trovere gasps. panting]
- [Baba Voss shushes]

548
00:35:40.601 --> 00:35:42.436
- Be still.
- [whimpers]

549
00:35:42.520 --> 00:35:43.937
Are you the ambassador?

550
00:35:44.021 --> 00:35:45.271
[panting continues]

551
00:35:45.355 --> 00:35:46.606
That's right.

552
00:35:46.690 --> 00:35:48.919
What is the meaning of this? Who are you?

553
00:35:49.527 --> 00:35:52.070
I will be asking the questions.
and you will be answering them.

554
00:35:52.154 --> 00:35:54.633
Wait. Ba... Baba Voss?

555
00:35:55.074 --> 00:35:56.218
What is this?

556
00:35:57.284 --> 00:35:58.638
- Harlan?
- Yeah.

557
00:35:59.161 --> 00:36:00.537
Baba Voss? [Gasps]

558
00:36:00.621 --> 00:36:03.290
- Oh. please. please don't kill me.
- He's not gonna kill you.

559
00:36:03.374 --> 00:36:06.793
Baba. release her now
or I'll have you thrown in jail.

560
00:36:06.877 --> 00:36:09.023
- Quiet.
- Have you lost your fucking mind?

561
00:36:09.547 --> 00:36:12.341
Harlan. shut up.
I'm not gonna ask you again.

562
00:36:12.425 --> 00:36:14.404
Good. 'cause it's getting annoying!

563
00:36:15.052 --> 00:36:16.906
Does Maghra even know you're here?

564
00:36:17.263 --> 00:36:19.640
- [Baba Voss] Does she know you're here?
- Fuck you.

565
00:36:19.724 --> 00:36:21.995
- [whistle blows]
- [Baba Voss grunts]

566
00:36:22.893 --> 00:36:23.935
- [grunts]
- [soldiers shouting]

567
00:36:24.019 --> 00:36:25.896
- [breathing shakily]
- That's a bad idea.

568
00:36:25.980 --> 00:36:28.649
[Baba Voss screams. grunts]

569
00:36:28.733 --> 00:36:30.275
- [soldiers shouting]
- [gasps]

570
00:36:30.359 --> 00:36:32.088
- [barks]
- [screams]

571
00:36:36.032 --> 00:36:37.177
[soldier shouts]

572
00:36:38.659 --> 00:36:40.263
- [soldier 2 shouts]
- [growls]

573
00:36:41.328 --> 00:36:42.955
[both grunting]

574
00:36:43.039 --> 00:36:44.934
- [bone snaps]
- [soldier 2 screams]

575
00:36:48.210 --> 00:36:50.170
- [Baba Voss shouts]
- [soldier 3 shouts]

576
00:36:50.254 --> 00:36:51.608
[grunts]

577
00:36:52.465 --> 00:36:54.986
[all grunting. shouting]

578
00:37:03.225 --> 00:37:06.164
- [grunting] Nice one. Nice.
- Nice. brother.

579
00:37:09.565 --> 00:37:12.609
[straining]

580
00:37:12.693 --> 00:37:13.837
[screams]

581
00:37:15.279 --> 00:37:17.967
[panting] The great traitor. Baba Voss.

582
00:37:20.993 --> 00:37:22.911
I will execute you where you stand.

583
00:37:22.995 --> 00:37:25.414
Ambassador. Ambassador.

584
00:37:25.498 --> 00:37:27.332
While you're rightfully upset
at the intrusion.

585
00:37:27.416 --> 00:37:28.709
I would just advise caution.

586
00:37:28.793 --> 00:37:31.295
- He attacked me.
- And he will be made to pay.

587
00:37:31.379 --> 00:37:33.130
- I'm just saying…
- [panting]

588
00:37:33.214 --> 00:37:36.300
…we're in the final stage of a peace
treaty you've worked so hard to achieve.

589
00:37:36.384 --> 00:37:38.719
There is no peace. You are a liar.

590
00:37:38.803 --> 00:37:41.138
Baba Voss.
you have never been one for words.

591
00:37:41.222 --> 00:37:43.056
Now is a good time
to keep your mouth shut.

592
00:37:43.140 --> 00:37:46.601
Her army is in Paya
with weapons of thunder and fire.

593
00:37:46.685 --> 00:37:49.396
Even now they are moving
across the Northern Mountains.

594
00:37:49.480 --> 00:37:52.399
For fuck's sake. Thunder and fire?
What are you talking about?

595
00:37:52.483 --> 00:37:55.819
I will not be called a liar
by this treasonous scum!

596
00:37:55.903 --> 00:37:57.047
[snarls]

597
00:37:57.530 --> 00:37:59.114
- [choking]
- [soldier grunts]

598
00:37:59.198 --> 00:38:01.553
Stop. all of you. by my command.

599
00:38:02.660 --> 00:38:04.472
And Maghra. Excellent.

600
00:38:05.329 --> 00:38:06.538
[Haniwa panting]

601
00:38:06.622 --> 00:38:08.601
- [soldier grunts]
- [Maghra] I said stop!

602
00:38:09.834 --> 00:38:11.312
Trovere.

603
00:38:12.420 --> 00:38:13.565
Please.

604
00:38:15.756 --> 00:38:16.798
Stand down.

605
00:38:16.882 --> 00:38:18.319
[gasps]

606
00:38:18.801 --> 00:38:20.989
- [bells jingle]
- Stand down.

607
00:38:21.429 --> 00:38:22.657
[whimpers]

608
00:38:24.098 --> 00:38:25.743
- Haniwa.
- [whimpering]

609
00:38:27.184 --> 00:38:28.727
In all my years.

610
00:38:28.811 --> 00:38:32.522
I have never witnessed such a blatant
breach of diplomatic protocols.

611
00:38:32.606 --> 00:38:35.712
He injured my soldiers.
and he attacked me in my own bed.

612
00:38:39.905 --> 00:38:41.426
[groans]

613
00:38:43.951 --> 00:38:47.599
Baba. what have you done?

614
00:38:48.956 --> 00:38:51.291
You are being deceived. my love.

615
00:38:51.375 --> 00:38:54.169
You've given me no time
to consider your words.

616
00:38:54.253 --> 00:38:55.796
You left me no choice.

617
00:38:55.880 --> 00:38:57.775
And you leave me with none.

618
00:38:58.549 --> 00:39:03.281
Your reckless behavior has put our peace
and the lives of every Payan at risk.

619
00:39:05.389 --> 00:39:06.932
Arrest Baba Voss immediately.

620
00:39:07.016 --> 00:39:08.809
Mama! No!

621
00:39:08.893 --> 00:39:11.436
[Maghra] Place him under guard at my house
until I return.

622
00:39:11.520 --> 00:39:13.772
If he resists. confine him to the dungeon.

623
00:39:13.856 --> 00:39:16.377
[Baba Voss]
It's all right. Haniwa. I will not resist.

624
00:39:20.112 --> 00:39:22.322
Ambassador Trovere. I assure you

625
00:39:22.406 --> 00:39:26.076
I would never do anything
to jeopardize the peace we have forged.

626
00:39:26.160 --> 00:39:29.121
Let me remind you.
in case you've forgotten.

627
00:39:29.205 --> 00:39:31.415
your sister murdered our peace delegates

628
00:39:31.499 --> 00:39:34.354
the last time our two nations met
under the terms of a truce.

629
00:39:35.044 --> 00:39:36.231
I understand.

630
00:39:36.796 --> 00:39:40.109
And believe me when I say
I am nothing like my sister.

631
00:39:41.175 --> 00:39:43.988
I hope you will accept my sincere apology.

632
00:39:44.428 --> 00:39:47.700
Forgive me if. at this moment.
I am not sure I will.

633
00:39:58.192 --> 00:39:59.420
When did he get back?

634
00:40:00.069 --> 00:40:01.631
- Tonight.
- [Harlan scoffs]

635
00:40:02.947 --> 00:40:05.407
Well. didn't waste any time. did he?

636
00:40:05.491 --> 00:40:06.636
Harlan.

637
00:40:07.284 --> 00:40:08.869
He may have just cost us everything.

638
00:40:08.953 --> 00:40:12.183
Harlan. what if he's right?

639
00:40:15.042 --> 00:40:19.524
You mean the Trivantians have
a new weapon of fire and thunder?

640
00:40:20.297 --> 00:40:21.423
But instead of attack us.

641
00:40:21.507 --> 00:40:23.550
they go all the way
into the Northern Mountains

642
00:40:23.634 --> 00:40:25.071
to attack one man?

643
00:40:28.723 --> 00:40:29.868
Yeah.

644
00:40:31.517 --> 00:40:33.872
I'll see what I can do
to soothe the ambassador.

645
00:40:43.070 --> 00:40:44.757
[inhales deeply]

646
00:40:48.409 --> 00:40:49.721
[sniffs]

647
00:40:58.294 --> 00:40:59.564
Whose baby is this?

648
00:41:00.838 --> 00:41:01.983
We need to talk.

649
00:41:04.467 --> 00:41:05.612
It is ours.

650
00:41:07.344 --> 00:41:08.489
No.

651
00:41:11.807 --> 00:41:12.952
Harlan.

652
00:41:13.392 --> 00:41:14.601
Of course not.

653
00:41:14.685 --> 00:41:16.228
- You may have abandoned me…
- [growls]

654
00:41:16.312 --> 00:41:17.854
…but I did not do the same.

655
00:41:17.938 --> 00:41:19.083
Then whose?

656
00:41:22.401 --> 00:41:24.005
His name is Wolffe.

657
00:41:24.987 --> 00:41:26.299
He's Kofun's.

658
00:41:27.865 --> 00:41:32.013
- Kofun's? [Groans]
- Baba. there's so much I have to tell you.

659
00:41:32.620 --> 00:41:33.704
[sighs deeply]

660
00:41:33.788 --> 00:41:36.476
Why is the baby with you?
Why is it not with the mother?

661
00:41:37.625 --> 00:41:40.335
The mother is Sibeth.

662
00:41:40.419 --> 00:41:43.316
- What? How is that?
- She seduced him.

663
00:41:44.507 --> 00:41:46.091
- She's a prisoner.
- Before that.

664
00:41:46.175 --> 00:41:48.510
Baba. we've been dealing with a lot
while you've been gone.

665
00:41:48.594 --> 00:41:50.448
[sighing] Oh. no. [Stammers]

666
00:41:51.138 --> 00:41:54.577
If this is Kofun's child.
then why is it not with him?

667
00:41:55.393 --> 00:41:58.414
He's having a hard time
accepting the child as his own.

668
00:41:59.021 --> 00:42:01.106
[Baba Voss sighs]

669
00:42:01.190 --> 00:42:03.044
And so the baby is in your care?

670
00:42:04.318 --> 00:42:05.463
Where's Paris?

671
00:42:09.907 --> 00:42:11.052
Where is Paris?

672
00:42:11.992 --> 00:42:13.243
[Baba Voss screaming]

673
00:42:13.327 --> 00:42:15.329
Sibeth!

674
00:42:15.413 --> 00:42:18.081
[screaming]

675
00:42:18.165 --> 00:42:19.894
[Maghra] Baba! Stop.

676
00:42:20.876 --> 00:42:23.837
We are turning Sibeth in
to the Trivantians in the morning.

677
00:42:23.921 --> 00:42:28.258
I promise you. nothing you would do
will compare to what they will do to her.

678
00:42:28.342 --> 00:42:30.655
- [growling] Sibeth!
- Baba. stop!

679
00:42:38.269 --> 00:42:40.081
- Where is she?
- Guards!

680
00:42:41.305 --> 00:43:41.683
